Head subcircular, with small frontal lamina of two separate sinuous lobes. Eyes absent. Antennae of four and six articles respectively (
Figure 2C
), both setose distally. Barbula (
Figure 2D
) with two lateral falcate projections on each side and one small triangular projection. Maxilliped (
Figure 2E
) almost semicircular, its anteromedial corner indented in place of palp (
Figure 2F
); its posterior article only half as large as anterior one and produced into tiny sharp plectron.

Pereomeres 3–5 fused dorsomedially, others distinct. Pereomeres 1–4 bearing coxal plates on both sides and prominent tergal projections on left sides; pereomeres 1 and 2 with dorsolateral bosses on right sides. Oostegites almost completely enclosing brood pouch; first oostegite (
Figure 2G,H
) with conspicuous outer groove and internal ridge bearing seven to eight irregular lobes along almost whole length; narrow posterior point sharp and curved. Pereopods of about same size, all their articles distinct; tuberculate ridge on basis of pereopod 2 (
Figure 2I
).

Pleon of six pleomeres, first four produced into lobed smooth-edged lateral plates on both sides, those on left side much smaller and narrower. Pleomere 5 bearing pair of spherical lateral plates. Final pleomere with fused spherical lateral plates. Pleopods 1–4 biramous with line of tubercles parallel to each edge (
Figure 2J
). Fifth pleopods and uropods uniramous and sparsely tuberculate.

Head subelliptical, bearing small dark eyes near posterolateral edges. Antennae of three and seven articles respectively, each with many setae distally; second antenna much longer than first, visible in dorsal view, its fifth and sixth articles setose (
Figure 2M
).

Pereomeres distinct, separated by deep anterolateral notches (
Figure 2K
). Pereopods of first pair largest and only ones with large dactyli; pereopods 2–4 progressively smaller, pereopods 4–7 of almost same size and shape (
Figure 2N
). Meri and carpi of pereopods 1–3 fused, others separated (
Figure 2L
).

Pleon of six pleomeres, narrowing smoothly posteriorly, lateral margins of all pleomeres reflexed laterally and posteriorly (
Figure 2K,L
). Five pairs of prominent uniramous flap-like pleopods progressively smaller posteriorly. Pleomere 6 produced into long flat extended uniramous uropods dorsally articulating.
